						<summary>

						<p>Three mutilated images lying in the Mallikārjuna temple.</p>						

						<p>The first image contains the name Yerabhūmanapalle Nalanāgi-reḍḍi Yerra[pa] of the Mudunūḷḷa-gōtram while the second has Prōlutula ma • • • • • Karnāṭi Malli-reḍḍi and the third has Peṁḍlimaṟṟi Tummala Nallaya.</p>						

						</summary>
